>>> Quote from nike+ exporter builder
The big lesson I take home is to focus on building
 on a pain you’ve definitely felt yourself.
  If that pain is shared by many, and your execution is good,
   the rest will follow. Because it’s a side project,
    try to keep it lean, cut the crap,
    and focus on providing a valuable service.
     You can really feel it when it’s solving a real issue.
      Heck, some might even ask you to build a paying version of it!


